textBeforeTable: The following ports are used by the Prime Collaboration Assurance (PCA) server to communicate either with the client machine or for the internal use. Internal Ports used by Prime Collaboration Assurance Server To receive traps (CSListener) if port 162 is occupied. 9000:UDP PCA Network Devices To receive syslogs 514:UDP PCA Network Devices To receive SNMP traps. 162:UDP PCA Network Devices To receive feedback/notification from Cisco VCS (HTTP). 8889:TCP PCA Cisco VCS To receive feedback/notification from Cisco VCS (HTTPS). 8886:TCP PCA Cisco VCS To receive syslog messages from Cisco 1040 sensors. 5666:UDP PCA Cisco 1040 Assurance Server (PCA) SMTP service. 25:TCP SMTP Server PCA NTP service. 123:UDP NTP Server PCA DNS service. 53:TCP
